Rugby greats Bryan Habana and Brian O’Driscoll teamed up to lead 100 hiking enthusiasts in the Drakensberg. JOHANNESBURG - Rugby greats Bryan Habana and Brian O’Driscoll teamed up to lead 100 hiking enthusiasts in the Drakensberg. This Laureus Sport For Good initiative raised well over R5-million during a four-day trek. READ: I was fit enough to keep playing, claims Habana Former Springbok winger Habana knows a thing or two about the power of Sport to inspire. So working with the Laureus Sports For Good Foundation to uplift others is something he is only happy to be part of.